{
  "texts": [
    "That is, one subanchor may be transformed into the other by isotopy of Σ which fixes all fiducial points.",
    "Proof: Let ϵ ⊂, ϵ ′ ⊂ ′ denote the edges connecting the anchor point to S 0 in either anchor.",
    "Since Ψ C depends only on the equivalence class of the anchor, the same is true for the representation Dr C. Therefore, without loss of generality, we may assume that \\ϵ = ′ \\ϵ ′.",
    "Moreover, we may assume that the edges ϵ, ϵ ′ have the same attaching point on S 0.",
    "Cutting Σ C along the common subanchor will connect all the interior boundary components, producing a surface homeomorphic to an annulus."
  ]
}